  "texts": [
    "We find that the fine-tuned SLMs 3 outperform the LLMs by an average 11.5% in accuracy across 15 subreddits.",
    "Among the fine-tuned SLMs, Mistral-NeMoinstruct, Gemma-2-9b, and Llama-3.1-8b show accuracies of 77.87%, 77.2%, and 72.5% respectively.",
    "Among LLMs, GPT-4o and GPT-4o-mini are the highest-performing models, both with an average accuracy of 65.8%.",
    "SLMs' performance is consistently superior, exhibiting higher accuracy than the LLMs across all subreddits.",
    "The highest and lowest average accuracy is achieved by the SLMs on r/changemyview (90.97%) and r/AskReddit (60.4%), and by the LLMs on r/movies (77.4%) and r/askscience (53.4%)."
